                     </persName>
                      
                  , <rs id="t17541204-4-viclabel20" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17541204-4-victim54 t17541204-4-viclabel20"></join>, did break and enter, and stealing out thence one promissory note of 
                     <persName id="t17541204-4-person55">
                        Agatha 
                        Child 
                     <interp inst="t17541204-4-person55" type="surname" value="Child"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17541204-4-person55" type="given" value="Agatha"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17541204-4-person55" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                   and Co. then bankers and partners, for 31 l. 10 s. being then due and unpaid, 40 guineas, 10 half-guineas, 10 thirty six-shilling pieces, the goods and money of Susannah Nobbs and 
                     
                        <persName id="t17541204-4-victim57" type="victimName">
                           Thomas 
                           Nobbs 
                        <interp inst="t17541204-4-victim57" type="surname" value="Nobbs"></interp>
